1> docker pull imagename : to pull an image from Docker Hub
2>docker -version : to check the version of Docker installed on your system
3> docker run imagename : to run a container from an image
4> docker run -d imagename -p 8080:80 : only run the container in the background and map port 8080 on the host to port 80 in the container
5> docker run -d imagename -p 8080:80 --name containername : to run the container in the background and map port 8080 on the host to port 80 in the container and give it a name
6> docker ps : to list all running containers
7> docker ps -a : to list all containers (running and stopped)
8> docker stop containername : to stop a running container
9> docker start containername : to start a stopped container
10>docker remove -f containername : to forcefully stop and  remove a container 
